Explanation:

For odd states, matching the interior $A sin(k x)$ to the exterior hyperbolic sine function yields $-k cot(k a) = -kappa coth(kappa(b-a))$, which simplifies directly to $k cot(k a) = -kappa coth(kappa(b-a))$.
